---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { t } from '../../i18n/ui';
import Container from '../../components/shared/Container.astro';

const lang = 'en';
---

<PageLayout
  title={t(lang, 'seo.about.title')}
  description={t(lang, 'seo.about.description')}
  lang={lang}
  canonicalPath="/en/about"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[60vh] md:min-h-[75vh] overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="/images/mors-founders.jpg"
      alt="Mathias and Johanne, founders of morˢ"
      fetchpriority="high"
      decoding="async"
      class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-deep-red/30 mix-blend-multiply"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-black/20 via-transparent to-black/30"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 h-1/3 bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent to-warm-white/50"></div>
    <Container>
      <div class="relative min-h-[60vh] md:min-h-[75vh] flex items-end pb-16 md:pb-24">
        <div class="animate-on-scroll">
          <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-5xl md:text-7xl text-warm-white drop-shadow-[0_2px_8px_rgba(0,0,0,0.35)]">
            About morˢ
          </h1>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="bg-warm-white py-24 md:py-40">
    <Container>
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-24">
        <div class="animate-on-scroll">
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-deep-red mb-8">
            Our story
          </h2>
          <div class="font-body font-light text-ink-light leading-loose space-y-6 text-lg">
            <p>
              Before Johanne met Mathias, she hadn&rsquo;t jumped on the coffee wagon herself.
              But Mathias&rsquo; curiosity and passion quickly rubbed off. He brought beans home
              from abroad and showed Johanne that whole new experiences open up when you
              approach the world of coffee a little differently.
            </p>
            <p>
              That&rsquo;s how the dream of creating a place grew &mdash; and it soon became
              something we would do together. We had long been in love with one particular
              spot: a listed half-timbered building from the 1600s on Klostergade 58, with red
              oak beams. When it suddenly became available, we seized it, and on Saturday 13
              June 2026 we opened the doors to morˢ.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Pull quote -->
        <div class="animate-on-scroll py-8">
          <blockquote class="font-display italic text-3xl md:text-4xl text-deep-red/80 text-center leading-snug max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            &ldquo;It shouldn&rsquo;t be pretentious. We make unseriously good coffee.&rdquo;
          </blockquote>
        </div>

        <div class="animate-on-scroll">
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-deep-red mb-8">
            The coffee
          </h2>
          <div class="font-body font-light text-ink-light leading-loose space-y-6 text-lg">
            <p>
              We nerd out on coffee in an unpretentious way. The beans come from IDEAL
              Kafferisteri in Herning &mdash; a microroaster that sources beans from small
              farms around the world and roasts them in small batches. That&rsquo;s why the
              coffee changes from season to season, and you can taste new beans all year round.
            </p>
            <p>
              We serve espresso-based coffee, batch brew and pour over, and the pastries come
              from a local micro-bakery. And in all modesty: we make a seriously good iced
              latte.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="animate-on-scroll">
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-deep-red mb-8">
            A labour of love
          </h2>
          <div class="font-body font-light text-ink-light leading-loose space-y-6 text-lg">
            <p>
              morˢ is built on family and close relationships &mdash; people who are almost as
              invested as we are. That&rsquo;s exactly why the place is called morˢ
              (&ldquo;mum&rsquo;s&rdquo;). Johanne&rsquo;s mum bakes the world&rsquo;s best
              brownie for the bar, her close friend&rsquo;s mum makes the ceramic cups for the
              coffee, and her stepmum&rsquo;s family has a coffee farm in Brazil that we hope to
              source beans from in time.
            </p>
            <p>
              We treat the space with great respect for the building&rsquo;s original character.
              The boulder in the middle of the room and the bare patches in the paint are part
              of the charm. There&rsquo;s room for 12 guests inside and a little outdoor seating
              on Klostergade &mdash; and of course coffee to-go for those passing by.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="animate-on-scroll">
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl text-deep-red mb-8">
            Our values
          </h2>
          <div class="font-body font-light text-ink-light leading-loose space-y-6 text-lg">
            <p>
              <strong class="text-ink font-normal">Good people first.</strong> You wouldn&rsquo;t
              be here if you weren&rsquo;t a good and kind person &mdash; and that matters most.
              Our values are a direction for the experience we want to give you.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-ink font-normal">We&rsquo;re not coffee snobs.</strong> We
              happily drink a good Nescafé Gold at home too. Just as you enjoy a nice steak on a
              Saturday and still love mac and sausages on a Tuesday, there&rsquo;s room for both
              in the world of coffee.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-ink font-normal">Embrace curiosity.</strong> We&rsquo;d love to
              help you learn what specialty coffee is and guide you towards new and different
              coffee. But we&rsquo;re not know-it-alls &mdash; in the end, it&rsquo;s a matter of
              taste.
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong class="text-ink font-normal">Service matters more than the coffee.</strong>
              We won&rsquo;t compromise on service to make a better cup. It&rsquo;s better to
              serve a bad cup of coffee than a bad experience.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
